This paper is primarily focused on game theory, specifically developing a framework for reasoning about strategic agents. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of computation in game theory, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also discusses conditions for the existence of equilibria, which could be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
